"""
PHASE 0 — MODEL 1 DATASET COLLECTOR
=====================================
Collects startup CPU + startup MEMORY labels for Model 1 training.

STEADY-STATE NOT COLLECTED — by design.
  Phase 2 uses the LIVE cgroup trace at runtime, not pre-collected data.
  The EWMA and 3σ formulas operate on real-time post-drop samples from
  the actual running pod. No offline steady-state measurement is needed.

TIMING OPTIMISATION (no-steady-state):
  Old: MAX_STARTUP(120) + DROP_CONFIRM(30) + buffer(10) = 160s worst-case
  New: MAX_STARTUP(120) + DROP_CONFIRM(5)  + buffer(5)  = 130s worst-case
  DROP_CONFIRM reduced 30→5s:
    - We only need to confirm the drop is real (not a momentary dip).
    - HOLD_S=20 already provides strong confirmation inside the detector.
    - The 5s post-detection buffer catches any immediate recovery.
    - Saves 25s per run × 450 runs = 11,250s = ~0.4h total.

  Old estimate: 1.7h  →  New estimate: ~1.3h  (25% faster)

CPU-drop detector (framework spec values — do not reduce)
----------------------------------------------------------
  DROP_FRAC=0.25, HOLD_S=20, MIN_STARTUP_S=10, MAX_STARTUP_S=120
  HOLD_S=20 is required: JVM class loading is not monotonic.
  A shorter hold window misses second spikes and mislabels them
  as steady-state, corrupting the startup_cpu_p99_m training label.

Requirements
------------
  sudo apt-get install -y skopeo docker.io
  pip install --break-system-packages psutil

Usage
-----
  sudo python3 phase0_model1_collector.py              # full run
  python3 phase0_model1_collector.py --metadata-only  # skopeo test only
  sudo python3 phase0_model1_collector.py --resume    # continue if interrupted
  sudo python3 phase0_model1_collector.py --fast      # 1 run per image (debug)
"""

